                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/102.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Willard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Inform Foreign Office that Department has done and is doing everything in its
                    power to protect lives and property of Spanish subjects in Mexico, and that
                    telegraphic instructions have been sent to Consuls at Hermosillo and Chihuahua
                    regarding subject matter your January 3, directing them to extend all possible
                    and proper protection to Spaniards.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
